#!perl

# PODNAME: dbic_critic
# ABSTRACT: Critique a database schema for best practices

package main;
use DBIx::Class::Schema::Critic;
my $critic = DBIx::Class::Schema::Critic->new_with_options();
$critic->critique();

=head1 USAGE

    dbic-critic --help
    dbic-critic --dsn dbi:Oracle:HR --username scott --password tiger

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This is the command line interface to
L<DBIx::Class::Schema::Critic|DBIx::Class::Schema::Critic>, a utility for
scanning a database schema for violations of best practices.

=head1 CONFIGURATION

Any command line options can also be specified in a configuration file and
loaded with the I<--configfile> option as per
L<MooseX::SimpleConfig|MooseX::SimpleConfig>.
